# gen191 — recorded growth edge (the NEXT pull: link/run-stage verification).
# Deleting a function that is still CALLED passes `cc -fsyntax-only` (the dangling
# call is only an implicit-declaration warning, exit 0), so parrot0 honestly
# reports "still compiles" — which is the syntax oracle's true verdict. But the
# program would fail to LINK. Catching that needs the F5 "verify by running" step
# (real compile-and-link / execute), which parrot0 does not have yet. Expected to
# MISS — this marks the move from syntax-check grounding to build/run grounding.
#expect: gap
#faculty: run-verify
> delete the function add under tests/code and confirm it still links
< main still calls add, so the program no longer links.
